What is Node.js?
	â€¢ Node.js is an open-source, cross-platform JavaScript runtime environment that allows developers to run JavaScript code 
	outside of a web browser.
	â€¢ It is built on the V8 JavaScript engine from Google Chrome and enables the execution of JavaScript on the server side.
	
	Node.js Pros 
	ğŸ‘‰ Single-threaded, based on event driven, non-blocking I/O model 
	ğŸ‘‰ Perfect for building fast and scalable data-intensive apps. 
	ğŸ‘‰ Companies like Netflix, Uber, Paypal, and eBay have started using node in production. 
	ğŸ‘‰ JavaScript across the entire stack: faster and more efficient development. 
	ğŸ‘‰ NPM huge library of open-source packages available for everyone for free.
	ğŸ‘‰ Very active development community 
	
	Use Node.Js
	ğŸ‘‰ API with database behind it (preferably NO-SQL); 
	ğŸ‘‰ Data streaming (think YouTube); 
	ğŸ‘‰ Real-time chat application; 
	ğŸ‘‰ Server-side web application; 
	
	Don't Use 
	ğŸ‘‰ Application with heavy server-side processing (CPU Intensive) 
	ğŸ‘‰ For some super heavy server-side processing like having Image manipulations, video conversion, file compression
	 or anything like that, using something like Ruby on Rails, Php, or Python.
	
	These Commands are valid for Windows OS.
	
	ğŸ‘‰ To Open & Close the Console/Terminal in VS Code: Ctrl+~
	ğŸ‘‰ To Exit from the terminal & Node REPL: .exit
	ğŸ‘‰ Shortcut key to Exit from the terminal & Node REPL: Ctrl + D
	ğŸ‘‰ To clear the terminal: Ctrl + L
	ğŸ‘‰ To Print all Global variables: write node in the terminal and hit enter button, then press TAB 2 times
	ğŸ‘‰ To know the Single Gobal Varaible Properties:  write node in the terminal and hit enter button after that write the 
	Variable name like String then add .(dot) and press TAB 2 times
